
[1]paronomasy

   PARONOM'ASY , n. [from Gr. to transgress law or rule.]

   A rhetorical figure, by which words nearly alike in sound, but of
   different meanings, are affectedly or designedly used; a play upon
   words; a pun. [See Pun.]
